16:
Uh-huh, another dream. Another
journey inside your head.
21:
Your dreams are always connected
to somewhere—
36: Oh, what's that? I'll dig it out!
90:
I'm sorry, I dragged you into my
dream!
94:
Please, run away! It's too dangerous
for you here!
98:
If this is a dream, I should be able to
move my arms and legs separately,
right?
102:
As long as it's something that you
can imagine! If you can't picture
yourself doing it, then...
130:
Come with us. Everything will be
okay!
164: W-waaah! We're going so high up!
190:
But this is a boat... and there's no
water...
193: It's fine. This is Marina's boat.
202:
No way! We're actually flying
through the sky!
241:
It's okay, Rooma. You're still you,
even if you can't remember all of
you.
245:
Stella's right! You're you, no matter
what.
250:
I-I guess so... And, um... Thanks for
saving me.
258: By the way, where are we?
262: This is my... and Stella's dream.
270:
I must've accidentally dragged you
into it... Rooma, where were you
before you came here?
274:
...In a small, cramped cylinder. I was
trapped in it for a long, long time.
277:
But then Capella took me out and
told me to go far, far away—
287: It'll be okay, Rooma. I'll protect you.
